{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877615157,"sessionID":"ses_285725935ffe2iFvlLwvsHGiKF","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8de2500011NHH3uAXGE503C","messageID":"msg_d7a8dc6d4001db4JY9GUz2pfwc","sessionID":"ses_285725935ffe2iFvlLwvsHGiKF","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-fae8c7df4d80459c8aa27e7b1b0c5229","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-025/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-025/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 |\n8: | Module | `cmd/cli` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: This AR implements the `MetadataService` and associated data models (`AgentMetadata` and `MetadataOptions`) that manage agent configuration throughout the CLI lifecycle. The service handles loading, saving, and validating YAML metadata files that persist agent state across `pack`, `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, and `status` operations.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ```\n20: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n21: │                         CLI Commands                                 │\n22: │  pack │ build │ publish │ invoke │ status                           │\n23: └─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n24:                       │\n25:                       ▼\n26: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n27: │                      Runtime Classes                                 │\n28: │  PackRuntime │ BuildRuntime │ PublishRuntime │ InvokeRuntime │      │\n29: │  StatusRuntime                                                       │\n30: └─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n31:                       │\n32:                       ▼\n33: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n34: │                      MetadataService                                 │\n35: │  - load_metadata(workspace_path) → AgentMetadata                    │\n36: │  - save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata) → None                   │\n37: │  - update_metadata(workspace_path, updates) → AgentMetadata         │\n38: │  - validate_workspace(workspace_path) → bool                        │\n39: └─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n40:                       │\n41:                       ▼\n42: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n43: │                      Data Models                                     │\n44: │  AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel) ← YAML serialization            │\n45: │  MetadataOptions (dataclass) ← CLI options mapping                  │\n46: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n47:                       │\n48:                       ▼\n49: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n50: │                      Storage                                         │\n51: │  {workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml (canonical)                        │\n52: │  {workspace}/agent.yaml (fallback)                                  │\n53: │  {workspace}/metadata.yaml (fallback)                               │\n54: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n55: ```\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## Data Structures\n60: \n61: ### AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\n62: \n63: Primary data model for agent configuration, stored as YAML.\n64: \n65: | Field | Type | Default | Description |\n66: |-------|------|---------|-------------|\n67: | `agent_name` | `str` | **required** | Unique name identifying the agent |\n68: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable summary |\n69: | `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Programming language used |\n70: | `entrypoint` | `str` | **required** | Command to launch the agent |\n71: | `port` | `int` | `8080` | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n72: | `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n73: | `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n74: | `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string for publishing |\n75: | `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Container image information |\n76: | `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Authentication configuration |\n77: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python dependency file |\n78: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry URL for image publishing |\n79: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n80: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n81: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent endpoint URL |\n82: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Workload Manager |\n83: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Router |\n84: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Path for the readiness probe |\n85: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port for the readiness probe |\n86: | `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n87: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | The session ID for the agent |\n88: | `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Kubernetes deployment information |\n89: \n90: #### Validators\n91: \n92: ```python\n93: @field_validator('language')\n94: @classmethod\n95: def validate_language(cls, v: str) -> str:\n96:     v = v.lower()\n97:     if v not in ['python', 'java']:\n98:         raise ValueError(f'language must be one of: python, java')\n99:     return v\n100: \n101: @field_validator('build_mode')\n102: @classmethod\n103: def validate_build_mode(cls, v: str) -> str:\n104:     v = v.lower()\n105:     if v not in ['local', 'cloud']:\n106:         raise ValueError(f'build_mode must be one of: local, cloud')\n107:     return v\n108: \n109: @field_validator('port')\n110: @classmethod\n111: def validate_port(cls, v: int) -> int:\n112:     if not (1 <= v <= 65535):\n113:         raise ValueError('port must be between 1 and 65535')\n114:     return v\n115: ```\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ### MetadataOptions (dataclass)\n120: \n121: CLI options dataclass for mapping command-line arguments to metadata fields.\n122: \n123: | Field | Type | Default |\n124: |-------|------|---------|\n125: | `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n126: | `language` | `Optional[str]` | `'python'` |\n127: | `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n128: | `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n129: | `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `'local'` |\n130: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n131: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n132: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n133: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n134: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n135: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n136: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n137: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n138: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n139: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n140: \n141: ```python\n142: @dataclass\n143: class MetadataOptions:\n144:     agent_name: Optional[str] = None\n145:     language: Optional[str] = 'python'\n146:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = None\n147:     port: Optional[int] = 8080\n148:     build_mode: Optional[str] = 'local'\n149:     requirements_file: Optional[str] = None\n150:     description: Optional[str] = None\n151:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n152:     router_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n153:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = \"\"\n154:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = 8080\n155:     registry_url: Optional[str] = \"\"\n156:     registry_username: Optional[str] = \"\"\n157:     registry_password: Optional[str] = \"\"\n158:     agent_endpoint: Optional[str] = \"\"\n159: \n160:     @classmethod\n161:     def from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\":\n162:         return cls(**{k: v for k, v in options.items() if v is not None})\n163: ```\n164: \n165: ---\n166: \n167: ## API Contracts\n168: \n169: ### MetadataService\n170: \n171: ```python\n172: class MetadataService:\n173:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n174:         self.verbose = verbose\n175:         self._metadata_filenames = [\n176:             \"agent_metadata.yaml\",\n177:             \"agent.yaml\",\n178:             \"metadata.yaml\",\n179:         ]\n180: \n181:     def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n182:         \"\"\"\n183:         Load metadata from workspace, falling back through filename list.\n184:         \n185:         Raises:\n186:             FileNotFoundError: If no metadata file exists\n187:             ValueError: If YAML content violates AgentMetadata schema\n188:         \"\"\"\n189: \n190:     def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n191:         \"\"\"\n192:         Save metadata to {workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml using yaml.dump.\n193:         \n194:         Settings:\n195:             - default_flow_style=False\n196:             - indent=2\n197:             - sort_keys=False\n198:             - model_dump(exclude_none=True)\n199:         \"\"\"\n200: \n201:     def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata:\n202:         \"\"\"\n203:         Load, apply updates, save, and return new AgentMetadata.\n204:         \"\"\"\n205: \n206:     def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool:\n207:         \"\"\"\n208:         Validate workspace structure and language-specific requirements.\n209:         \n210:         Returns:\n211:             True if valid\n212:             \n213:         Raises:\n214:             ValueError: If workspace invalid\n215:         \"\"\"\n216: \n217:     def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n218:         \"\"\"\n219:         Check for at least one *.py file in workspace root.\n220:         \n221:         Raises:\n222:             ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")\n223:         \"\"\"\n224: \n225:     def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None:\n226:         \"\"\"\n227:         Check for pom.xml in workspace.\n228:         \n229:         Raises:\n230:             ValueError(\"No pom.xml found in workspace\")\n231:         \"\"\"\n232: ```\n233: \n234: ---\n235: \n236: ### Metadata File Format\n237: \n238: ```yaml\n239: agent_name: my-agent\n240: description: A sample agent\n241: language: python\n242: entrypoint: python main.py\n243: port: 8080\n244: build_mode: local\n245: version: v1.0.0\n246: requirements_file: requirements.txt\n247: registry_url: \"\"\n248: registry_username: \"\"\n249: registry_password: \"\"\n250: agent_endpoint: null\n251: workload_manager_url: null\n252: router_url: null\n253: readiness_probe_path: null\n254: readiness_probe_port: null\n255: agent_id: null\n256: session_id: null\n257: image:\n258:   name: my-agent\n259:   tag: latest\n260:   id: sha256:...\n261:   size: 150MB\n262:   build_time: 45s\n263: auth:\n264:   type: bearer\n265: k8s_deployment:\n266:   type: AgentRuntime\n267:   namespace: default\n268:   deployment_name: my-agent\n269:   service_name: my-agent-service\n270:   node_port: 30001\n271: ```\n272: \n273: ---\n274: \n275: ## Error Handling\n276: \n277: ### Exception Types\n278: \n279: | Exception | Scenario |\n280: |-----------|----------|\n281: | `FileNotFoundError` | Workspace or metadata file not found |\n282: | `ValueError` | Schema validation failure, missing required field |\n283: | `pydantic.ValidationError` | Pydantic field validation failure |\n284: \n285: ### Error Handling Patterns\n286: \n287: ```python\n288: def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata:\n289:     for filename in self._metadata_filenames:\n290:         path = workspace_path / filename\n291:         if path.exists():\n292:             try:\n293:                 with open(path, 'r') as f:\n294:                     data = yaml.safe_load(f)\n295:                 return AgentMetadata(**data)\n296:             except yaml.YAMLError as e:\n297:                 raise ValueError(f\"Invalid YAML in {filename}: {e}\")\n298:             except ValidationError as e:\n299:                 raise ValueError(f\"Schema validation failed: {e}\")\n300:     \n301:     raise FileNotFoundError(\n302:         f\"No metadata file found in {workspace_path}. \"\n303:         f\"Expected one of: {', '.join(self._metadata_filenames)}\"\n304:     )\n305: ```\n306: \n307: ---\n308: \n309: ## Testing Strategy\n310: \n311: ### Unit Tests\n312: \n313: | Test Case | Description |\n314: |-----------|-------------|\n315: | `test_load_metadata_primary` | Load from `agent_metadata.yaml` |\n316: | `test_load_metadata_fallback_agent_yaml` | Fallback to `agent.yaml` |\n317: | `test_load_metadata_fallback_metadata_yaml` | Fallback to `metadata.yaml` |\n318: | `test_load_metadata_not_found` | Raise `FileNotFoundError` when all missing |\n319: | `test_load_metadata_invalid_yaml` | Raise `ValueError` on malformed YAML |\n320: | `test_load_metadata_schema_validation` | Raise `ValueError` on Pydantic validation failure |\n321: | `test_save_metadata_excludes_none` | Verify `exclude_none=True` behavior |\n322: | `test_save_metadata_yaml_format` | Verify YAML formatting (indent, no flow style) |\n323: | `test_update_metadata_partial` | Update specific fields only |\n324: | `test_validate_python_workspace` | Check for `*.py` files |\n325: | `test_validate_java_workspace` | Check for `pom.xml` |\n326: | `test_validate_language_python` | Validate `language='python'` |\n327: | `test_validate_language_java` | Validate `language='java'` |\n328: | `test_validate_language_invalid` | Reject invalid language |\n329: | `test_validate_build_mode_local` | Validate `build_mode='local'` |\n330: | `test_validate_build_mode_cloud` | Validate `build_mode='cloud'` |\n331: | `test_validate_port_range` | Validate port 1-65535 |\n332: | `test_validate_port_out_of_range` | Reject port outside range |\n333: | `test_metadata_options_from_options` | Create MetadataOptions from dict |\n334: \n335: ### Integration Tests\n336: \n337: | Test Case | Description |\n338: |-----------|-------------|\n339: | `test_pack_loads_metadata` | PackRuntime uses MetadataService.load_metadata |\n340: | `test_pack_saves_metadata` | PackRuntime uses MetadataService.save_metadata |\n341: | `test_build_updates_version` | BuildRuntime increments version in metadata |\n342: | `test_publish_updates_deployment_info` | PublishRuntime updates `k8s_deployment` |\n343: | `test_invoke_reads_endpoint` | InvokeRuntime reads `agent_endpoint` from metadata |\n344: | `test_status_reads_metadata` | StatusRuntime loads metadata for status check |\n345: \n346: ---\n347: \n348: ## File Structure\n349: \n350: ```\n351: cmd/cli/\n352: ├── agentcube/\n353: │   ├── models/\n354: │   │   ├── __init__.py              # Module marker\n355: │   │   └── pack_models.py           # MetadataOptions dataclass\n356: │   ├── services/\n357: │   │   ├── __init__.py              # Services package docstring\n358: │   │   └── metadata_service.py      # AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n359: │   ├── runtime/\n360: │   │   ├── pack_runtime.py          # Uses MetadataService\n361: │   │   ├── build_runtime.py         # Uses MetadataService\n362: │   │   ├── publish_runtime.py       # Uses MetadataService\n363: │   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py        # Uses MetadataService\n364: │   │   └── status_runtime.py        # Uses MetadataService\n365: │   └── ...\n366: └── tests/\n367:     ├── test_metadata_service.py     # MetadataService unit tests\n368:     ├── test_agent_metadata.py       # AgentMetadata model tests\n369:     ├── test_pack_models.py          # MetadataOptions tests\n370:     └── integration/\n371:         └── test_metadata_flow.py    # Integration tests\n372: ```\n373: \n374: ---\n375: \n376: ## Dependencies\n377: \n378: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n379: |---------|---------|---------|\n380: | `pydantic` | >=2.0.0 | BaseModel, validators, serialization |\n381: | `pyyaml` | >=6.0 | YAML load/dump |\n382: | `pathlib` | stdlib | Path handling |\n383: \n384: ---\n385: \n386: ## Implementation Notes\n387: \n388: ### Constants\n389: \n390: ```python\n391: METADATA_FILENAMES = [\"agent_metadata.yaml\", \"agent.yaml\", \"metadata.yaml\"]\n392: CANONICAL_METADATA_FILENAME = \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n393: SUPPORTED_LANGUAGES = [\"python\", \"java\"]\n394: SUPPORTED_BUILD_MODES = [\"local\", \"cloud\"]\n395: DEFAULT_PORT = 8080\n396: ```\n397: \n398: ### YAML Serialization\n399: \n400: ```python\n401: yaml.dump(\n402:     metadata.model_dump(exclude_none=True),\n403:     default_flow_style=False,\n404:     indent=2,\n405:     sort_keys=False,\n406: )\n407: ```\n408: \n409: ### Language Validation\n410: \n411: Lowercase normalization before validation:\n412: ```python\n413: language = options.get('language', 'python').lower()\n414: ```\n415: \n416: ---\n417: \n418: ## References\n419: \n420: - cli-toolkit/design.md — CLI toolkit architecture\n421: - cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification (workspace validation, metadata format)\n\n(End of file - total 421 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThis AR implements the `MetadataService` and associated data models (`AgentMetadata` and `MetadataOptions`) that manage agent configuration throughout the CLI lifecycle. The service handles loading, saving, and validating YAML metadata files that persist agent state across `pack`, `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, and `status` operations.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-025/design.md","time":{"start":1775877615127,"end":1775877615155}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877615159,"sessionID":"ses_285725935ffe2iFvlLwvsHGiKF","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8ddee9001IP3SclJYfNZ748","messageID":"msg_d7a8dc6d4001db4JY9GUz2pfwc","sessionID":"ses_285725935ffe2iFvlLwvsHGiKF","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-98930da437a346898af7836c48daaa2e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-025/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-025/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型\n2: \n3: ## 概述\n4: \n5: | 属性 | 值 |\n6: |------|-----|\n7: | AR | AR-025 |\n8: | Module | cmd/cli |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. Purpose (目的)\n15: \n16: Implement the `MetadataService` and Pydantic data models (`AgentMetadata`, `MetadataOptions`) that form the core configuration layer of AgentCube CLI. These components provide structured YAML-based metadata management for agent lifecycle operations (pack, build, publish, invoke, status), enabling:\n17: \n18: 1. **Metadata Persistence**: Load/save agent configuration as YAML with fallback file names\n19: 2. **Schema Validation**: Enforce field constraints via Pydantic validators (language, build_mode, port)\n20: 3. **Workspace Validation**: Verify workspace structure based on language (Python *.py, Java pom.xml)\n21: 4. **CLI Option Mapping**: Map Typer CLI options to metadata updates via `MetadataOptions` dataclass\n22: \n23: **Current State**: No dedicated metadata service or data models exist. CLI commands directly handle YAML files without schema validation, leading to inconsistent metadata handling and potential configuration errors.\n24: \n25: **Target State**: \n26: - `MetadataService` class with load/save/update/validate methods\n27: - `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model with 20+ fields and validators\n28: - `MetadataOptions` dataclass for CLI-to-metadata option mapping\n29: - Consistent error handling for invalid metadata files\n30: - Unit test coverage for validation scenarios\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## 2. Scope (范围)\n35: \n36: ### 2.1 In Scope\n37: \n38: | Deliverable | Description |\n39: |-------------|-------------|\n40: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `MetadataService` class for metadata lifecycle management |\n41: | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass for CLI options |\n42: | `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package exports |\n43: | `tests/test_metadata_service.py` | Unit tests for MetadataService |\n44: | `tests/test_agent_metadata.py` | Unit tests for AgentMetadata validators |\n45: \n46: ### 2.2 MetadataService Methods\n47: \n48: | Method | Purpose |\n49: |--------|---------|\n50: | `__init__(verbose)` | Initialize service with verbose logging flag |\n51: | `load_metadata(workspace_path)` | Load `AgentMetadata` from YAML with fallback filenames |\n52: | `save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)` | Persist metadata to `agent_metadata.yaml` |\n53: | `update_metadata(workspace_path, updates)` | Apply partial updates and return new metadata |\n54: | `validate_workspace(workspace_path)` | Validate workspace directory and file structure |\n55: | `_validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)` | Check for *.py files in Python workspace |\n56: | `_validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)` | Check for pom.xml in Java workspace |\n57: \n58: ### 2.3 AgentMetadata Model Fields\n59: \n60: | Field | Type | Default | Validation |\n61: |-------|------|---------|------------|\n62: | `agent_name` | `str` | Required | Unique agent identifier |\n63: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable summary |\n64: | `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Validator: `['python', 'java']` lowercase |\n65: | `entrypoint` | `str` | Required | Command to launch agent |\n66: | `port` | `int` | `8080` | Validator: `1..65535` |\n67: | `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | Validator: `['local', 'cloud']` lowercase |\n68: | `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n69: | `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version for publishing |\n70: | `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Container image info |\n71: | `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Authentication config |\n72: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python dependency file |\n73: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry URL for publishing |\n74: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n75: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n76: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent endpoint URL |\n77: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Workload Manager URL |\n78: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Router URL |\n79: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Readiness probe path |\n80: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Readiness probe port |\n81: | `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n82: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Session ID for agent |\n83: | `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Kubernetes deployment info |\n84: \n85: ### 2.4 MetadataOptions Fields\n86: \n87: | Field | Type | Default |\n88: |-------|------|---------|\n89: | `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n90: | `language` | `Optional[str]` | `'python'` |\n91: | `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n92: | `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n93: | `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `'local'` |\n94: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n95: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n96: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n97: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n98: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n99: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n100: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n101: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n102: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n103: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n104: \n105: ### 2.5 Out of Scope\n106: \n107: | Item | Reason |\n108: |------|--------|\n109: | Database-backed metadata storage | YAML file storage per spec; database would be separate feature |\n110: | Metadata encryption/secrets | Security handled by separate secret management (future) |\n111: | Multi-agent metadata aggregation | Single agent per workspace per spec |\n112: | Version history tracking | Git handles versioning; metadata file is single state |\n113: | Cloud metadata sync | Metadata is local file; cloud sync would be separate feature |\n114: \n115: ---\n116: \n117: ## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n118: \n119: ### 3.1 新增文件\n120: \n121: ```\n122: cmd/cli/\n123: ├── agentcube/\n124: │   ├── models/\n125: │   │   ├── __init__.py           # NEW: models package marker\n126: │   │   └── pack_models.py        # NEW: MetadataOptions dataclass\n127: │   ├── services/\n128: │   │   ├── __init__.py           # MODIFY: export MetadataService, AgentMetadata\n129: │   │   └── metadata_service.py   # NEW: MetadataService class\n130: │   └── runtime/\n131: │   │   └── pack_runtime.py       # MODIFY: use MetadataService\n132: │   └── cli/\n133: │       └── main.py               # MODIFY: use MetadataOptions for pack command\n134: └── tests/\n135:     ├── test_metadata_service.py  # NEW: MetadataService unit tests\n136:     └── test_agent_metadata.py    # NEW: AgentMetadata validator tests\n137: ```\n138: \n139: ### 3.2 Upstream Dependencies\n140: \n141: | Dependency | Version | Impact |\n142: |------------|---------|--------|\n143: | `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | BaseModel for AgentMetadata; validators for field constraints |\n144: | `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | YAML load/dump for metadata file persistence |\n145: | `pathlib` | stdlib | Path handling for workspace validation |\n146: | Standard library `logging` | stdlib | Verbose logging support |\n147: \n148: ### 3.3 Downstream Consumers\n149: \n150: | Consumer | Method Usage |\n151: |----------|--------------|\n152: | `PackRuntime` | `MetadataService.load_metadata()`, `save_metadata()`, `validate_workspace()` |\n153: | `BuildRuntime` | `MetadataService.load_metadata()`, `update_metadata()` for version increment |\n154: | `PublishRuntime` | `MetadataService.load_metadata()`, `update_metadata()` for deployment info |\n155: | `InvokeRuntime` | `MetadataService.load_metadata()` for endpoint retrieval |\n156: | `StatusRuntime` | `MetadataService.load_metadata()` for status display |\n157: | CLI `pack` command | `MetadataOptions.from_options()` for CLI option mapping |\n158: \n159: ### 3.4 Breaking Change Considerations\n160: \n161: - **Metadata file name**: Primary filename is `agent_metadata.yaml`; fallbacks are `agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml`\n162: - **Schema validation**: Existing metadata files must conform to new validators; invalid language/build_mode will raise errors\n163: - **Required fields**: `agent_name` and `entrypoint` are now required; existing files missing these will fail validation\n164: - **Port validation**: Port must be 1-65535; values outside range will be rejected\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n169: \n170: ### Alternative 1: dataclasses instead of Pydantic\n171: \n172: **Approach**: Use Python `dataclasses` for `AgentMetadata` with manual validation methods.\n173: \n174: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n175: |--------|------------|\n176: | Pros | No external dependency; simpler for basic data structures |\n177: | Cons | No automatic validation; more boilerplate; no serialization helpers; no type coercion |\n178: \n179: **Decision**: Rejected. Pydantic provides automatic validation, type coercion, and `model_dump()` for serialization without boilerplate.\n180: \n181: ### Alternative 2: JSON-based metadata storage\n182: \n183: **Approach**: Store metadata as JSON instead of YAML.\n184: \n185: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n186: |--------|------------|\n187: | Pros | Native Python `json` module; no pyyaml dependency; easier machine parsing |\n188: | Cons | Less human-readable; no comments support; spec explicitly requires YAML |\n189: \n190: **Decision**: Rejected. Spec requires YAML format (`agent_metadata.yaml`) for human-readable configuration with comments.\n191: \n192: ### Alternative 3: Single metadata file in home directory\n193: \n194: **Approach**: Store all agent metadata in a central file (e.g., `~/.agentcube/metadata.yaml`) instead of workspace-local files.\n195: \n196: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n197: |--------|------------|\n198: | Pros | Centralized management; easier multi-agent overview |\n199: | Cons | Workspace independence lost; harder to version control; spec requires per-workspace file |\n200: \n201: **Decision**: Rejected. Spec requires `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` for workspace-local configuration and Git version control.\n202: \n203: ### Alternative 4: Configuration file inheritance/templating\n204: \n205: **Approach**: Support base metadata file with inheritance (e.g., `extends: base-metadata.yaml`).\n206: \n207: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n208: |--------|------------|\n209: | Pros | Reuse common settings; reduce duplication |\n210: | Cons | Adds complexity; not in spec; inheritance resolution overhead |\n211: \n212: **Decision**: Rejected for initial scope. May add as enhancement if users request configuration reuse patterns.\n213: \n214: ---\n215: \n216: ## 5. Risks\n217: \n218: | Risk | Mitigation |\n219: |------|------------|\n220: | Invalid YAML syntax | `yaml.safe_load` raises `YAMLDecodeError`; catch and re-raise with context |\n221: | Missing required fields | Pydantic `ValidationError` with field-specific messages |\n222: | Unknown fields in YAML | Pydantic `extra=\"ignore\"` (or forbid per spec requirement) |\n223: | Workspace validation race condition | Check file existence before validation; handle `FileNotFoundError` |\n224: | Language mismatch | `_validate_python_workspace` / `_validate_java_workspace` with clear error messages |\n225: | Port range violation | Pydantic validator `validate_port` raises `ValueError` with valid range |\n226: \n227: ---\n228: \n229: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n230: \n231: - [ ] Create `agentcube/models/__init__.py` package marker\n232: - [ ] Create `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` with `MetadataOptions` dataclass\n233: - [ ] Implement `MetadataOptions.from_options(options: Dict[str, Any])` factory method\n234: - [ ] Create `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` with `MetadataService` class\n235: - [ ] Implement `MetadataService.__init__(verbose: bool = False)`\n236: - [ ] Implement `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` with fallback filenames\n237: - [ ] Implement `MetadataService.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)` with YAML options\n238: - [ ] Implement `MetadataService.update_metadata(workspace_path, updates)` partial update\n239: - [ ] Implement `MetadataService.validate_workspace(workspace_path)` structure check\n240: - [ ] Implement `_validate_python_workspace` for *.py file check\n241: - [ ] Implement `_validate_java_workspace` for pom.xml check\n242: - [ ] Define `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model with all fields\n243: - [ ] Implement `validate_language` validator (python/java lowercase)\n244: - [ ] Implement `validate_build_mode` validator (local/cloud lowercase)\n245: - [ ] Implement `validate_port` validator (1-65535 range)\n246: - [ ] Update `agentcube/services/__init__.py` exports\n247: - [ ] Update `PackRuntime` to use `MetadataService`\n248: - [ ] Add unit tests for metadata load/save with valid YAML\n249: - [ ] Add unit tests for fallback filename behavior\n250: - [ ] Add unit tests for Pydantic validators\n251: - [ ] Add unit tests for workspace validation scenarios\n252: - [ ] Run `pytest tests/test_metadata_service.py` to validate\n253: \n254: ---\n255: \n256: ## 7. References\n257: \n258: - Spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md` — Requirement: Metadata file format, Workspace validation\n259: - Design: `cli-toolkit/design.md` — MetadataService, AgentMetadata, MetadataOptions signatures\n260: - AR-021 — CLI pack command (uses MetadataService for pack flow)\n261: - AR-022 — CLI publish command (uses metadata for deployment info)\n262: - Pydantic Documentation: https://docs.pydantic.dev/\n263: - PyYAML Documentation: https://pyyaml.org/wiki/PyYAMLDocumentation\n\n(End of file - total 263 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-025 |\n| Module | cmd/cli |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\nImplement the `MetadataService` and Pydantic data models (`AgentMetadata`, `MetadataOptions`) that form the core configuration layer of AgentCube CLI. These components provide structured YAML-based metadata management for agent lifecycle operations (pack, build, publish, invoke, status), enabling:\n\n1. **Metadata Persistence**: Load/save agent configuration as YAML with fallback file names\n2. **Schema Validation**: Enforce field constraints via Pydantic validators (language, build_mode, port)\n3. **Workspace Validation**: Verify workspace structure based on language (Python *.py, Java pom.xml)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-025/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775877615124,"end":1775877615157}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877615162,"sessionID":"ses_285725935ffe2iFvlLwvsHGiKF","part":{"id":"prt_d7a8dea05001zjiX4QgDR6HLbi","messageID":"msg_d7a8dc6d4001db4JY9GUz2pfwc","sessionID":"ses_285725935ffe2iFvlLwvsHGiKF","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-1b060f5a46484d3ab9206c67066e8dc3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-025/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-025/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型 |\n8: | Module | `cmd/cli` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: AgentMetadata Model (ST-1)\n18: \n19: - [x] **T1.1**: Implement `AgentMetadata` Pydantic BaseModel with all required fields\n20:   - Purpose: Define primary data model for agent configuration stored as YAML\n21:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py:8-30`\n22:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestAgentMetadata::test_agent_metadata_valid -v`\n23: \n24: - [x] **T1.2**: Implement `language` field validator\n25:   - Purpose: Validate language is one of ['python', 'java'] with lowercase normalization\n26:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py:32-39`\n27:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestAgentMetadata::test_agent_metadata_invalid_language -v`\n28: \n29: - [x] **T1.3**: Implement `build_mode` field validator\n30:   - Purpose: Validate build_mode is one of ['local', 'cloud'] with lowercase normalization\n31:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py:41-48`\n32:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestAgentMetadata::test_agent_metadata_invalid_build_mode -v`\n33: \n34: - [x] **T1.4**: Implement `port` field validator\n35:   - Purpose: Validate port is in range 1-65535\n36:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py:50-55`\n37:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestAgentMetadata::test_agent_metadata_invalid_port_low -v`\n38: \n39: ### Phase 2: MetadataOptions Dataclass (ST-2)\n40: \n41: - [x] **T2.1**: Implement `MetadataOptions` dataclass with all CLI options fields\n42:   - Purpose: Define dataclass for mapping command-line arguments to metadata fields\n43:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py:6-21`\n44:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions; print(MetadataOptions.__dataclass_fields__)\"`\n45: \n46: - [x] **T2.2**: Implement `MetadataOptions.from_options()` factory method\n47:   - Purpose: Create MetadataOptions from dict filtering None values\n48:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py:23-26`\n49:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.models.pack_models import MetadataOptions; opt = MetadataOptions.from_options({'agent_name': 'test', 'port': 8080}); print(opt.agent_name)\"`\n50: \n51: ### Phase 3: MetadataService Core Methods (ST-3)\n52: \n53: - [x] **T3.1**: Implement `MetadataService.__init__` with verbose flag\n54:   - Purpose: Initialize service with verbose flag for logging control\n55:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py:59-60`\n56:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestMetadataService::test_metadata_service_load_agent_metadata_yaml -v`\n57: \n58: - [x] **T3.2**: Implement `load_metadata()` with fallback filename list\n59:   - Purpose: Load metadata from workspace, falling back through ['agent_metadata.yaml', 'agent.yaml', 'metadata.yaml']\n60:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py:62-72`\n61:   - Verification: